args:
Elias has told no one of the monster in his
dreams. When he embraces his dark feelings
after practice, the massive fiend suddenly
appears from the space between worlds,
forcing the prince to go there and defeat it.
Wait, is that an otherworld fragment?\nWhy would this be here?
Guess that fiend we just defeated\ndropped it.
Interesting. Well, for now let's head back\nand let everyone know what happened.
...You defeated a fiend THAT strong?!\nWowsers! You guys are nuts!
Your head will pop if it swells any more.
Still, this whole thing is very strange...
I've never heard of fiends like that\nappearing in this area before.
Indeed, I believe it's quite unusual for\nfiends to press the attack in a single\narea as they did.
It's almost as though they're gathering in\nthis place for some reason.
Perhaps something is attracting them to\nthis place.
But that's only one of the mysteries we\nneed to solve.
The other one being why the fiends keep\ngetting stronger?
Yes. Something must be providing them\nwith that power.
And it may be the same thing that's calling\nthem here in the first place.
That certainly makes sense, although it's\nall still hypothetical at the moment.
Well, we'll have to solve all of these\nmysteries if we want to be sure the\ntown is safe.
Then let us give it our all! With any luck,\nwe'll be able to completely wipe out the\nfiends and perform our recital.
At least cover yer mouth, kid. Sheesh.\nYou not gettin' enough sleep or somethin'?
There was a monster...and darkness...\nIt's all kind of fuzzy now.
I have to go to practice.
Go get 'em, kid! But hey, don't push yerself\nTOO hard, yeah?
Nightmares, huh? I guess even folks with\ngodly voices still have worries like the\nrest of us.
Yeah, when yer that age, ya get worked up\nabout all kinds'a stuff—some of it real\nand some of it not.
Learning to overcome it is what makes a\nperson an adult.
And I wanna learn from Lucretia so I can\nALSO be a really good singer!
The order of arrival is meaningless!\nIt certainly doesn't give you the right\nto monopolize Lucretia all to yourself!
Plus, you can practice solos until you're\nhoarse. It won't change anything.
I'm going to sing the solo! Me!
B-but I was gonna work really hard...\nWaaaaaaah!
Now, now! I have time to watch both of\nyou, so let's try to get along.
We'll start by having you sing, Pia.
Mmm. Very good, both of you. However...
Pia, your lack of confidence is manifesting\nitself in your singing voice.
You must have more faith in yourself.\nENJOY your singing. Do you understand?
Yes, ma'am! I'll do my best!
Now Elias, you demonstrated exceptional\nskill. In fact, I wish I could do nothing but\nsit here and let your voice wash over me.
Oh wow. I actually got praised by Lucretia!\nThis is great!
But now I want you to focus on placing \nmore gravitas in your voice. For example...
As ever, Lucretia is second to none.
You're both from the same year in the\nchoir, right?
Yes. We used to compete all the time.\nAh, memories.
You must have been pretty great if you\nwere able to hang with that! So why'd\nyou decide to become a baton guy?
If you mean a conductor, it's because\nI had to stop singing when my voice\nchanged.
Instead, I altered my focus and apprenticed\nmyself to a master conductor.
Oh, right. Because only kids with soprano\nvoices can sing in the choir.
But in the end, it worked out just dandy\nbecause you became a super awesome\nbaton guy!
Er, yes. Though I'd honestly never even\nconsidered such a thing when I was with\nthe choir.

I gave everything to my singing—and
because of that, I lost sight of who I really
was. Honestly, I was an incredibly difficult
person to deal with.
(I know Lucretia liked my singing, but my\nthroat keeps getting worse...)
I'm going to lose my place at this rate.\nThere won't be anywhere for me to go!
Huh?! Wh-what was that sound?!\nDid it come from the mountains?
Get rid of it... GET RID OF IT!
That voice... Is that the monster from\nmy nightmares?!
All will disappear! All will vanish!\nGET RID OF IT AAAAALL!
What's this thing groaning about?\nGet back in there, you!
Welp, that didn't work. Probably just a\nmatter of time before this thing comes out\nfrom the space between worlds, huh?
If that happens, the town is going to\nsuffer severe damage during the fight.
I don't get this. So was the fiend what\ndropped the otherworld fragment just\nthis thing's lackey or somethin'?
The otherworld fragment... Wait, that's it!\nWe'll use the fragment!
We'll turn the tables on this thing and go\nINTO the space between worlds!
And in doing so seize the offensive.
That's the idea. Now come on, everyone!
